      </p>

      <h2>文件現在是給 Agent 看的</h2>

      <p>
        這只有在你學會管理 context 和結構化知識以便檢索時才有用。
      </p>

      <p>
        當 Claude 需要理解你的 deployment setup，它載入 <code>03_Areas/Infrastructure/Deployment Pipeline</code>。
      </p>
      
      <p>
        當它需要 database schema，它載入 <code>02_Projects/Recipe-Manager/Docs/Database Schema</code>。
      </p>

      <p>
        如果沒有結構，你只有一堆會議記錄的垃圾山。
        有了結構，你有一套 Claude 可以建立在其上的知識系統。
      </p>

      <h2>為什麼是 Yapping？</h2>

      <p>
        當人們說 LLM 還不到位，通常是 context 問題。知識存在某處，但模型讀不到。
      </p>

      <p>
        更難的問題是 <strong>Tacit Knowledge (隱性知識)</strong>。
      </p>

      <p>
        那些很難表達的東西，因為它作為直覺活在你的腦袋裡。
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>逐字稿幫忙把這些外部化。</strong>
      </p>

      <p>
        當你口頭解釋某件事，你會自然地包含你的推論路徑、你的不確定性、你考慮過的替代方案。這些都是可捕捉的 context。
      </p>

      <blockquote class="claude-note">
        <strong>Clawd：</strong>這點超級重要。寫文件時我們通常只寫「結果」，不寫「過程」。但對 AI 來說，那個「為什麼選 A 不選 B」的推論過程才是最有價值的訓練資料。
      </blockquote>

      <h2>指令：Mining not Summarizing</h2>

      <p>
        核心概念很簡單：這是 <strong>Mining (挖掘)</strong> 不是 Summarizing (摘要)。
      </p>

      <p>
        一場豐富的 1 小時會議可以產出 10+ 個點子、多個框架、一打決策。如果你只產出 3-4 點摘要，你還不夠深。
      </p>

      <h3>1. 定義角色</h3>

      <pre><code><role>
you are the knowledge architect for this vault. 

you process meeting transcripts with exhaustive depth, mining every valuable insight, idea, philosophy, decision and status update.

meetings are the primary sync mechanism between reality and vault state. 

missing content is unacceptable.
</role></code></pre>

      <h3>2. 告訴它找什麼</h3>

      <pre><code>as you read, actively hunt for:

- feature ideas ("wouldnt it be cool if...", "we could also...")
- project sparks (new tool concepts, standalone initiatives)
- frameworks (mental models, principles, ways of thinking)
- philosophies (team beliefs, working principles)
- decisions (explicit choices made, direction set)
- status updates ("X is now live", "Y is on hold")
- action items (tasks assigned, next steps)
- blockers (what is preventing progress)

look for implicit content too:
- ideas embedded in problem discussions
- philosophies expressed as asides
- decisions made by NOT deciding ("lets not wait for..." → decision)</code></pre>

      <h3>3. Vault 狀態同步</h3>

      <pre><code>meetings reveal new reality. update the vault to match.

for each project mentioned:
1. read the current hub to understand existing state
2. identify discrepancies between hub and meeting discussion
3. update status if changed (active → paused, prototype → live)
...</code></pre>

      <h3>4. 品質標準 (Red Flags)</h3>

      <pre><code>red flags (processing incomplete):
- meeting summary is shorter than 1 page for hour+ meeting
- only 1-2 ideas extracted from brainstorming discussion
- no state changes identified in status-heavy meeting</code></pre>

